dcterms:creator: J. E. Beasley
dcterms:description: The ORLIB datasets contain instances with 100, 250, 500, and 1000 nodes, where integral coefficients of the Q matrix are randomly chosen from the uniform distribution [-100,100]. These datasets are sparse with linear and quadratic density of 10%.
dcterms:title: ORLIB datasets

dcterms:creator: G. Palubeckis
dcterms:description: The Palubeckis datasets consist of larger and denser datasets with 3000, 4000, 5000, 6000, and 7000 nodes, with density ranging from 10% to 100%. These datasets are used for testing optimization algorithms.
dcterms:title: Palubeckis datasets

dcterms:creator: J. B. Ghosh
dcterms:description: MDPLIB consists of instances related to the Maximum Diversity Problem, including 315 instances categorized into small, medium, and large sizes. The dataset is used for testing optimization algorithms.
dcterms:title: MDPLIB
